00185 static void rna_Object_matrix_local_set(PointerRNA *ptr, const float values[16])
00186 {
00187     Object *ob = ptr->id.data;
00188 
00189     /* localspace matrix is truly relative to the parent, but parameters
00190      * stored in object are relative to parentinv matrix.  Undo the parent
00191      * inverse part before updating obmat and calling apply_obmat() */
00192     if (ob->parent) {
00193         float invmat[4][4];
00194         invert_m4_m4(invmat, ob->parentinv);
00195         mult_m4_m4m4(ob->obmat, invmat, (float(*)[4])values);
00196     }
00197     else {
00198         copy_m4_m4(ob->obmat, (float(*)[4])values);
00199     }
00200 
00201     /* don't use compat so we get predictable rotation */
00202     object_apply_mat4(ob, ob->obmat, FALSE, FALSE);
00203 }

00324 static void rna_Object_data_set(PointerRNA *ptr, PointerRNA value)
00325 {
00326     Object *ob = (Object*)ptr->data;
00327     ID *id = value.data;
00328 
00329     if (id == NULL || ob->mode & OB_MODE_EDIT)
00330         return;
00331 
00332     if (ob->type == OB_EMPTY) {
00333         if (ob->data) {
00334             id_us_min((ID*)ob->data);
00335             ob->data = NULL;
00336         }
00337 
00338         if (id && GS(id->name) == ID_IM) {
00339             id_us_plus(id);
00340             ob->data = id;
00341         }
00342     }
00343     else if (ob->type == OB_MESH) {
00344         set_mesh(ob, (Mesh*)id);
00345     }
00346     else {
00347         if (ob->data)
00348             id_us_min((ID*)ob->data);
00349         if (id)
00350             id_us_plus(id);
00351 
00352         ob->data = id;
00353         test_object_materials(id);
00354 
00355         if (GS(id->name) == ID_CU)
00356             test_curve_type(ob);
00357         else if (ob->type == OB_ARMATURE)
00358             armature_rebuild_pose(ob, ob->data);
00359     }
00360 }

00864  * logic from check_body_type()

00866 static int rna_GameObjectSettings_physics_type_get(PointerRNA *ptr)
00867 {
00868     Object *ob = (Object*)ptr->id.data;
00869 
00870     /* determine the body_type setting based on flags */
00871     if (!(ob->gameflag & OB_COLLISION)) {
00872         if (ob->gameflag & OB_OCCLUDER) {
00873             ob->body_type = OB_BODY_TYPE_OCCLUDER;
00874         }
00875         else if (ob->gameflag & OB_NAVMESH) {
00876             ob->body_type = OB_BODY_TYPE_NAVMESH;
00877         }
00878         else {
00879             ob->body_type = OB_BODY_TYPE_NO_COLLISION;
00880         }
00881     }
00882     else if (ob->gameflag & OB_SENSOR) {
00883         ob->body_type = OB_BODY_TYPE_SENSOR;
00884     }
00885     else if (!(ob->gameflag & OB_DYNAMIC)) {
00886         ob->body_type = OB_BODY_TYPE_STATIC;
00887     }
00888     else if (!(ob->gameflag & (OB_RIGID_BODY|OB_SOFT_BODY))) {
00889         ob->body_type = OB_BODY_TYPE_DYNAMIC;
00890     }
00891     else if (ob->gameflag & OB_RIGID_BODY) {
00892         ob->body_type = OB_BODY_TYPE_RIGID;
00893     }
00894     else {
00895         ob->body_type = OB_BODY_TYPE_SOFT;
00896         /* create the structure here because we display soft body buttons in the main panel */
00897         if (!ob->bsoft)
00898             ob->bsoft = bsbNew();
00899     }
00900 
00901     return ob->body_type;
00902 }

00904 static void rna_GameObjectSettings_physics_type_set(PointerRNA *ptr, int value)
00905 {
00906     Object *ob = (Object*)ptr->id.data;
00907     const int was_navmesh = (ob->gameflag & OB_NAVMESH);
00908     ob->body_type = value;
00909 
00910     switch (ob->body_type) {
00911     case OB_BODY_TYPE_SENSOR:
00912         ob->gameflag |= OB_SENSOR|OB_COLLISION|OB_GHOST;
00913         ob->gameflag &= ~(OB_OCCLUDER|OB_DYNAMIC|OB_RIGID_BODY|OB_SOFT_BODY|OB_ACTOR|OB_ANISOTROPIC_FRICTION
00914                           |OB_DO_FH|OB_ROT_FH|OB_COLLISION_RESPONSE|OB_NAVMESH);
00915         break;
00916     case OB_BODY_TYPE_OCCLUDER:
00917         ob->gameflag |= OB_OCCLUDER;
00918         ob->gameflag &= ~(OB_SENSOR|OB_RIGID_BODY|OB_SOFT_BODY|OB_COLLISION|OB_DYNAMIC|OB_NAVMESH);
00919         break;
00920     case OB_BODY_TYPE_NAVMESH:
00921         ob->gameflag |= OB_NAVMESH;
00922         ob->gameflag &= ~(OB_SENSOR|OB_RIGID_BODY|OB_SOFT_BODY|OB_COLLISION|OB_DYNAMIC|OB_OCCLUDER);
00923 
00924         if (ob->type == OB_MESH) {
00925             /* could be moved into mesh UI but for now ensure mesh data layer */
00926             BKE_mesh_ensure_navmesh(ob->data);
00927         }
00928 
00929         break;
00930     case OB_BODY_TYPE_NO_COLLISION:
00931         ob->gameflag &= ~(OB_SENSOR|OB_RIGID_BODY|OB_SOFT_BODY|OB_COLLISION|OB_OCCLUDER|OB_DYNAMIC|OB_NAVMESH);
00932         break;
00933     case OB_BODY_TYPE_STATIC:
00934         ob->gameflag |= OB_COLLISION;
00935         ob->gameflag &= ~(OB_DYNAMIC|OB_RIGID_BODY|OB_SOFT_BODY|OB_OCCLUDER|OB_SENSOR|OB_NAVMESH);
00936         break;
00937     case OB_BODY_TYPE_DYNAMIC:
00938         ob->gameflag |= OB_COLLISION|OB_DYNAMIC|OB_ACTOR;
00939         ob->gameflag &= ~(OB_RIGID_BODY|OB_SOFT_BODY|OB_OCCLUDER|OB_SENSOR|OB_NAVMESH);
00940         break;
00941     case OB_BODY_TYPE_RIGID:
00942         ob->gameflag |= OB_COLLISION|OB_DYNAMIC|OB_RIGID_BODY|OB_ACTOR;
00943         ob->gameflag &= ~(OB_SOFT_BODY|OB_OCCLUDER|OB_SENSOR|OB_NAVMESH);
00944         break;
00945     default:
00946     case OB_BODY_TYPE_SOFT:
00947         ob->gameflag |= OB_COLLISION|OB_DYNAMIC|OB_SOFT_BODY|OB_ACTOR;
00948         ob->gameflag &= ~(OB_RIGID_BODY|OB_OCCLUDER|OB_SENSOR|OB_NAVMESH);
00949 
00950         /* assume triangle mesh, if no bounds chosen for soft body */
00951         if ((ob->gameflag & OB_BOUNDS) && (ob->boundtype<OB_BOUND_TRIANGLE_MESH)) {
00952             ob->boundtype = OB_BOUND_TRIANGLE_MESH;
00953         }
00954         /* create a BulletSoftBody structure if not already existing */
00955         if (!ob->bsoft)
00956             ob->bsoft = bsbNew();
00957         break;
00958     }
00959 
00960     if (was_navmesh != (ob->gameflag & OB_NAVMESH)) {
00961         if (ob->type == OB_MESH) {
00962             /* this is needed to refresh the derived meshes draw func */
00963             DAG_id_tag_update(ptr->id.data, OB_RECALC_DATA);
00964         }
00965     }
00966 
00967     WM_main_add_notifier(NC_OBJECT|ND_DRAW, ptr->id.data);
00968 }
